   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Expands the `reject-reason` field in `testmempoolaccept` responses to include `m_debug_message` from `ValidationState`. This compound string is also the complete error message thrown by the mempool in resposne to `sendrawtransaction`.\r\n\r\nThe extra verbosity is helpful to consumers of `testmempoolaccept`, which is sort of a debug tool anyway. The beginning of these messages remains the same (`m_reject_reason`) and so although this may be a breaking API change for consumers who expect exact strings, that should be easy to fix (after reading the release notes ð¬). \r\n\r\nold: `insufficient fee`\r\nnew: `insufficient fee, rejecting replacement dafc2bb343e7598c625de0c83ae9594eecab2c6252d08dd19b9d39e5b5402800; less fees than conflicting txs; 3.00 < 4.00`\r\n",
